snippet.textDisplay: This is the issue with live service games, they entirely rely on the dev's, hr and community to thrive. The dev's implement things into the game, adding content and such. The higher ups decide quality, quantity and what they think the minimum is. The community have power over both, without a community a game simply cannot thrive, the community decides if a game is worth the time, worth their time and money. If the player decides its not worth their time and money then they will leave, quit the game, leaving a negative impact. Epic Games no matter how they feel, in the end the community takes priority over the dev's and higher ups. As I've said already, the players are the deciding factor on if a game is good or not, sure the dev's help push the train but in the end only the players can ultimately decide the fate of a game, especially a live service game. This is what's going on with games such as Destiny 2, The dev's aren't pumping out the quality and quantity needed, the higher ups won't do quality control and the community wont play the game because its simply not worth the time and money.
